# hello-fade-in.note

A minimal "hello" title that fades in, holds, then fades out. Use this as a starting
point for any single-title open / close card. Brief follows the structure the editor
expects when you paste it into the Note (markdown) field of a new clip.

---

**Target duration:** 5 s
**Aspect:** 9:16 (vertical short)
**Camera hint:** static, centered

**Scene prompt (paste into Generate panel)**:

> hello fade-in titled HELLO at center, dark background, 5 seconds @ 30fps

**References** (paste into the References list, one per line):

- bold sans-serif, very large (~220px)
- pure black background, white text
- fade in over the first half-second, hold, fade out in the last half-second

**Why this clip works as a hello**

- It uses only `useCurrentFrame` + `interpolate` from Remotion — no extra deps, no
  external fonts, no image assets. The agent can write it in one shot and you can
  preview it without any setup beyond `bun run dev`.
- The output is intentionally boring: if you can render this, the SDK + Player
  pipeline is healthy. Iterate from here.
